args:
Despite Mei Hou Wang possibly being a fiend,
Wu Kong begins to befriend him. But then
Zhu Bajie and Sha Wujing show up, claiming
to have come at Xuan Zang's request
in order to lay his new companion low.
Glad we made it outta that place.\nStill, are we SURE it's a good idea\nto be takin' the fiend guy with us?
Aw, he doesn't seem like a bad guy.\nPlus, we don't know for SURE that\nhe's a fiend, right?
I surveyed the flow of mana, and he is\ndefinitely not a normal human, Qilin,\nor any other race I have encountered.
The mysteries continue to mount.\nCould there possibly be such a thing\nas a kind-hearted fiend?
It's a strange case for sure.
Hey, speaking of the maybe-devil,\nwhere did he and Wu Kong go?
Ah, there you are. Were you able to\nsafely reunite with your friends?
(This guy said he was Mei Hou Wang,\nbut he actually seems pretty...decent?)
Hey, so have we met before?
If so, I don't recall it. I'm sorry.
I FEEL like I have, but I can't say that\nwith any kind of complete positivity.
I see... Do you think perhaps I truly\nam a fiend, as your friends suspect?
Did I hurt living beings like the\ncreature that attacked me?
Eh, don't worry about it. Even if you ARE\nsome kind of fiend, it's not a problem\nso long as you're a good guy.
I wonder... But thank you regardless.
Oh, hey! I haven't even introduced myself!\nI'm Wu Kong, and I'm a rookie sealer\nout on a solo journey of training.
It is good to meet you, Wu Kongâ€”and\nquite impressive that one so small as\nyourself is traveling alone.
Yeah, I've been all over. Taiwu...\nAlberia... Even the northern lands!
You must have seen a great many things.
Not especially. It's merely that\nyou are so different from myself.
I don't have memories, you see.\nI don't have... Well, anything.
Hey, you know what? Come with me!

You're gonna be my travel buddy!
If you don't have any memories,
then it's time to go on a journey
and MAKE yourself some!
I traveled the world with my own master,\nwhich is what made me how I am now.
I mean, even if we just kill some time\nwhile waiting for your memory to return,\nit'll STILL be fun on a bun!
Heh... It might be, at that.
Hey! They heck are you guys DOING?!\nWait a second... You're...
Long time no see, Wu Kong.
HmmMMM, yes. You appear to have\nbecome a bit more able in the many\nyears since our paths have crossed.
Are you all right? Who are these men?
Zhu Bajie and Sha Wujing. They're old\nacquaintances of Master Xuan Zang.
Well, more like uninvited hangers-on\nthan acquaintances, I guess.
She always said non-sealers shouldn't get\ninvolved with Qilin relics, but these two\njust REFUSE to take the very obvious hint.
They keep following her around no matter\nwhere she goes and ranting about owing\nher a debt for...something or other.
Bwa ha ha! It's like the wife always says:\nLeave no debt unpaid.
I do what's right. That's my code.
Code? Right? Such things have fallen\nout of fashion in these times, old friend.
I have little interest in repaying favorsâ€”\ninstead, I seek to probe the deepest\nsecrets of the Qilin relics!
But more to the point, what are you doing\nhere, and why the hell are you ATTACKING\npoor Mei Hou Wang?!
We came on Master Xuan Zang's orders.
Oh, come on! She'd never order you\nto just show up and attack somebody!

Yeah, but she DID tell us, and I quote,
ï¼‚We can't simply leave Mei Hou Wang be.ï¼‚
Which is clearly a nice way of saying,
ï¼‚Give him the ol' dirt nap, will you?ï¼‚
That is NOT what that means at ALL!
